legEmissionsDetails":[]},"remarkList":[{"modifiedDate":"2021-07-01T14:19:27.893","modifiedByFull":"Masembo, Miguel","remark":"Operational comments : \n\t\n\tVessel loaded from Odudu, Nigeria and discharge the full cargo in Point Tupper, however, the voyage was generated basis two disport, net days decreased accdly.\n\tNil demurrage incurred on completion of the voyage, the earning improved slightly as the port cost and bunker cons/cost were all lesser than estimated.\n\tPort cost basis PDA about $88K lesser than estimated and bunker cons/cost $165k also lesser than estimated.\n\t\n\tImprovements: \n\nAll in all straight forward voyage.\n\nFixture comments :\n\nVESSEL                               Almi Sky\nCHARTERER                      P66\nCP DATE                            May 18, 2021\nBROKER                             Howe Robinson\nOPERATOR                        Miguel\nREF                                     VOY 2021-01\nCARGO                              130KT NHC\nLAYCAN                             June 1-2\nLOAD                                 1/2 SP WAF\nDISCHARGE                       1/2 SP USAC\nBALLAST FROM                Singapore \nRATE                                  ws50\nEXPECTED DAILY              - $ 3,313 pd\nDEMURRAGE                    $ 24,000 pd\nTD20 Benchmark             $ 3,000 pd @ ws52.5\nVessel on TD20                - $ 3,984 pd @ ws52.5\nVOYAGE DAYS                  69 days\nNEXT OPEN                       USAC - end June\nVOYAGE LADEN               C/P Speed About 12 Knots WSNP \nWe got stranded in a dismal WAF market ballasting in from the East.  There was black hole during our fixing window with very few cargoes to work.  \nThe above includes $20k hull cleaning in Singapore after the last voyage.  We have some upside potential with better consumption than what is in Q88. \n It\u2019s not pretty, however the market has fallen 5 points since we went on subs last week - so it could have been worse if you can imagine."},{"modifie